              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-14104",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2025-14104\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: util-linux\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2025-14104](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-14104)\nA flaw was found in util-linux. This vulnerability allows a heap buffer overread when processing 256-byte usernames, specifically within the `setpwnam()` function, affecting SUID (Set User ID) login-utils utilities writing to the password database.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2025-14104**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|util-linux||[CVE-2025-14104](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-14104)|\n\nA flaw was found in util-linux. This vulnerability allows a heap buffer overread when processing 256-byte usernames, specifically within the `setpwnam()` function, affecting SUID (Set User ID) login-utils utilities writing to the password database."
              },
              "properties": {
