            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-3184",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "util-linux: util-linux: Access control bypass due to improper hostname canonicalization"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in util-linux. Improper hostname canonicalization in the `login(1)` utility, when invoked with the `-h` option, can modify the supplied remote hostname before setting `PAM_RHOST`. A remote attacker could exploit this by providing a specially crafted hostname, potentially bypassing host-based Pluggable Authentication Modules (PAM) access control rules that rely on fully qualified domain names. This could lead to unauthorized access."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-3184",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-3184\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: util-linux\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-3184](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-3184)\nA flaw was found in util-linux. Improper hostname canonicalization in the `login(1)` utility, when invoked with the `-h` option, can modify the supplied remote hostname before setting `PAM_RHOST`. A remote attacker could exploit this by providing a specially crafted hostname, potentially bypassing host-based Pluggable Authentication Modules (PAM) access control rules that rely on fully qualified domain names. This could lead to unauthorized access.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-3184**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|util-linux||[CVE-2026-3184](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-3184)|\n\nA flaw was found in util-linux. Improper hostname canonicalization in the `login(1)` utility, when invoked with the `-h` option, can modify the supplied remote hostname before setting `PAM_RHOST`. A remote attacker could exploit this by providing a specially crafted hostname, potentially bypassing host-based Pluggable Authentication Modules (PAM) access control rules that rely on fully qualified domain names. This could lead to unauthorized access."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "2.0",
                "tags": [
                  "vulnerability",
                  "security",
                  "LOW"
                ]
              }
